eland]]\n", "text_old": "{{Unreferenced|date=May 2019|bot=noref (GreenC bot)}}\nThe [[European route E01]] in the [[Republic of Ireland]] is a serie of roads, part of the [[International E-road network]] running in an north south axis on the Irish east coast. It runs through five [[Counties of Ireland|counties]] starting on the [[United Kingdom|British]] border with the province of [[Northern Ireland]] at [[Dundalk]], coming from [[Belfast]] and [[Larne]]. It passes the capital [[Dublin]] until it stops at [[Rosslare Harbour]] in Southern [[Republic of Ireland|Ireland]]. From there the E01 crosses the [[Celtic Sea]] and the [[Bay of Biscay]] on a non-existent [[ferry]] towards [[Spain]] and [[Portugal]].\n\n== Route ==\nThe [[European route E01|E01]] comes from [[Northern Ireland]] when it crosses the border at [[Dundalk]] where the [[United Kingdom|British]] [[A1 road (Northern Ireland)|A1 road]] changes to the [[Republic of Ireland|Irish]] N1 road until northern [[Dundalk]]. It then follows the [[M1 motorway (Republic of Ireland)|M1 motorway]] to [[Drogheda]] and eventually the [[capital city|capital]] [[Dublin]]. After using the [[M50 motorway (Ireland)|M50]] ring road around [[Dublin]], the E01 uses the [[N11 road (Ireland)|N11 road]] and [[M11 motorway (Republic of Ireland)|M11 motorway]] passing [[Bray, County Wicklow|Bray]], [[Wicklow]], [[Gorey]] and [[Enniscorthy]] to [[Wexford]]. The last part is the [[N25 road (Ireland)|N25 road]] towards [[Rosslare Harbour]]. The E01 covers a total distance of 266&nbsp;km (165&nbsp;mi) in the [[Republic of Ireland]].\n\n== Detailed route ==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|+<big>E01 Dundalk - Rosslare</big>\n!County\n!National\nroad\n\nnumber\n!Section\n!Junction\n|-\n|{{Flagicon|United Kingdom}}{{Flagicon|Northern Ireland}}\n|[[File:UK road A1.svg|frameless|38x38px]] [[A1 road (Northern Ireland)|A1 road]]\n| colspan=\"2\" |{{Flag|UK}} from [[Larne]] to border with Republic of Ireland via [[Belfast]], [[Lisburn]] and [