tegory:2020 in Portugal]]\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in Europe|Portugal]]\n", "text_old": "{{Current disaster|event=pandemic|date=January 2020}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{EngvarB|date=March 2020}}\n{{short description|Details of ongoing viral pandemic in Portugal}}\n{{Infobox pandemic\n| name            = 2020 coronavirus pandemic in Portugal\n| map1            = COVID-19 Outbreak Cases in Portugal by municipalities.png\n| legend1         = Map of municipalities with coronavirus cases (as of 5 April 2020):<ref name=\"DGS\"/>\n<table style=\"width:50px;white-space:nowrap;\"><!--\n<tr><td>{{colorbox|#510000}}</td><td>{{right|\u22653000 confirmed cases}}</td></tr>\n-->\n<tr><td>{{colorbox|#900000}}</td><td>{{right|300-2999 confirmed cases}}</td></tr>\n<tr><td>{{colorbox|#c80200}}</td><td>{{right|30-299 confirmed cases}}</td></tr>\n<tr><td>{{colorbox|#ee7070}}</td><td>{{right|3-29 confirmed cases}}</td></tr>\n<tr><td>{{colorbox|#ffC0C0}}</td><td>{{right|1-3 confirmed cases}}</td></tr>\n<tr><td>{{colorbox|#666666}}</td><td>{{right|0 confirmed cases}}</td></tr>\n</table>\n| map2            = \n| legend2         = \n| map3            = \n| legend3         = \n| disease         = [[COVID-19]]\n| virus_strain    = [[SARS-CoV-2]]\n| location        = [[Portugal]]\n| first_case      = [[Porto]]\n| arrival_date    = 2 March 2020<br />({{Age in years, months, weeks and days |month1= 3|day1=2|year1=2020}})\n| origin          = [[Wuhan]], [[China]]\n| recovery_cases  = 140<ref name=\"DGS\"/>\n| deaths          = 311<ref name=\"DGS\"/>\n| confirmed_cases = 11,730<ref name=\"DGS\">{{cite web|url=https://covid19.min-saude.pt/ponto-de-situacao-atual-em-portugal/|website=covid19.min-saude.pt|language=pt|title=Ponto de Situa\u00e7\u00e3o em Portugal}}</ref>\n| suspected_cases = 91,794<ref name=\"DGS\"/>\n| severe_cases    = 270<ref name=\"DGS\"/>\n| total_ili       = \n| website         = {{URL|https://covid19.min-saude.pt}}\n}}\nThe ongoing [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic|global pandemic]] of [[severe acute respiratory syndrome coronavirus 2]] (SARS-CoV-2), which causes [[coronavirus disease 2019]] (COVID-19), was confirmed to have reached [[Portugal]] in March 2020, by the [[Directorate-General of Health]] (DGS).<ref name=\"dn_coronavirus_portugal\" />\n\n== Background ==\nOn 12 January, the [[World Health Organization]] (WHO) confirmed that a [[novel coronavirus]] was the cause of a respiratory illness in a cluster of people in Wuhan City, Hubei Province, China, who had initially come to the attention of the WHO on 31 December 2019. This cluster was initially linked to the [[Huanan Seafood Wholesale Market]] in Wuhan City. However, some of those first cases with laboratory confirmed results had no link to the market, and the source of the epidemic is unknown.<ref name=\"Elsevier\">{{cite web|url=https://www.elsevier.com/connect/coronavirus-information-center|title=Novel Coronavirus Information Center|last=Elsevier|date=|website=Elsevier Connect|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200130171622/https://www.elsevier.com/connect/coronavirus-information-center|archive-date=30 January 2020|access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"Reynolds4March2020\">{{Cite news|last=Reynolds|first=Matt|url=https://www.wired.co.uk/article/china-coronavirus|title=What is coronavirus and how close is it to becoming a pandemic?|date=4 March 2020|work=Wired UK|access-date=5 March 2020|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200305104806/https://www.wired.co.uk/article/china-coronavirus|archive-date=5 March 2020|issn=1357-0978}}</ref>\n\nUnlike [[Severe acute respiratory syndrome|SARS of 2003]], the [[Case fatality rate|case fatality ratio]] for COVID-19 <ref name=\"Imperial13March2020\">{{cite web|url=https://www.imperial.ac.uk/news/196137/crunching-numbers-coronavirus/|title=Crunching the numbers for coronavirus|website=Imperial News|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200319084913/https://www.imperial.ac.uk/news/196137/crunching-numbers-coronavirus/|archive-date=19 March 2020|access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"Gov.ukHCIDDef\">{{cite web|url=https://www.gov.uk/guidance/high-consequence-infectious-diseases-hcid|title=High consequence infectious diseases (HCID); Guidance and information about high consequence infectious diseases and their management in England|last=|first=|date=|website=GOV.UK|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200303051938/https://www.gov.uk/guidance/high-consequence-infectious-diseases-hcid|archive-date=3 March 2020|access-date=17 March 2020}}</ref> has been much lower, but the [[Transmission (medicine)|transmission]] has been significantly greater, with a significant total death toll.<ref name=\"WFSA\">{{cite web|url=https://www.wfsahq.org/resources/coronavirus|title=World Federation Of Societies of Anaesthesiologists \u2013 Coronavirus|last=|first=|date=|website=www.wfsahq.org|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200312233527/https://www.wfsahq.org/resources/coronavirus|archive-date=12 March 2020|access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"Imperial13March2020\" /> COVID-19 typically appears with about seven days of [[Influenza-like illness|flu-like symptoms]] followed by some people progressing to symptoms of a [[viral pneumonia]] requiring admission to hospital.<ref name=\"Imperial13March2020\" /> From 19 March, COVID-19 was no longer classified as a \"High consequence infectious disease\".<ref name=\"Gov.ukHCIDDef\" />\n\n== Alert level ==\n\nOn 12 March 2020, the Portuguese government declared the highest level of alert because of [[Coronavirus disease 2019|COVID-19]] and will maintain it until 9 April.<ref>{{Cite news|last=|first=|url=https://expresso.pt/coronavirus/2020-03-13-Covid-19.-Estado-de-alerta-ate-pelo-menos-9-de-abril|title=Covid-19. Estado de alerta at\u00e9 pelo menos 9 de abril|date=13 March 2020|work=Expresso|access-date=13 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> [[Portugal]] enters a Mitigation Phase as Community [[Transmission (medicine)|Transmission]] is detected and there is a need to implement harsher measures.{{citation needed|date=March 2020}}\n\nOn 18 March, the [[President of Portugal|President of the Republic]], [[Marcelo Rebelo de Sousa]], declared the entirety of the Portuguese territory in a [[State of emergency#Portugal|State of Emergency]] for the following fifteen days, with the possibility of renewal, the first since the [[Carnation Revolution]] in 1974.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.presidencia.pt/?idc=22&idi=176060 |title=Mensagem do Presidente da Rep\u00fablica ao Pa\u00eds sobre a declara\u00e7\u00e3o do estado de emerg\u00eancia (Pal\u00e1cio de Bel\u00e9m, 18 de mar\u00e7o de 2020) |trans-title=Message of the President of the Republic to the Country on the declaration of a state of emergency |date=18 March 2020 |website=Presidency of the Portuguese Republic |language=pt |accessdate=18 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 24 March, the Portuguese Government admitted that the country could not contain [[Coronavirus disease 2019|COVID-19]] any more, as it is widespread, and, on 26 March, the country entered the '''Mitigation Stage.''' The health care sites dedicated to fight the disease started including the Portugal [[Community health center|Health centers groups]] (''agrupamentos de centros de sa\u00fade'', ACES).<ref>{{Cite news|last=|first=|url=https://expresso.pt/coronavirus/2020-03-24-Portugal-em-fase-de-mitigacao-a-partir-de-quinta-feira|title=Portugal em fase de mitiga\u00e7\u00e3o a partir de quinta-feira|date=24 March 2020|work=Expresso|access-date=|language=pt|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 2 April, the [[Assembly_of_the_Republic_(Portugal)|Parliament]] approved<ref>{{Cite news|last=|first=|url=https://24.sapo.pt/atualidade/artigos/parlamento-aprova-renovacao-do-estado-de-emergencia|title=Parlamento aprova prolongamento do estado de emerg\u00eancia at\u00e9 17 de abril|date=2 April 2020|work=Sapo|access-date=2 April 2020|language=pt|url-status=live}}</ref> the extension of the State of Emergency, requested by the President.<ref>{{Cite document|url=http://www.presidencia.pt/archive/doc/Projeto_Decreto_do_PR_Renovacao_Estado_de_Emergencia_20200401.pdf|title=Projeto do Decreto do Presidente da Rep\u00fablica de Renova\u00e7\u00e3o do Estado de Emerg\u00eancia|language=pt}}</ref> The State of Emergency will remain until 17 April, subject to further extensions of similar duration.\n\n== Information ==\nUsually you can find information about [[Coronavirus disease 2019|COVID-19]] under the [[Directorate-General of Health|DGS]] home site. But because of the increasing severity of the pandemic one site was created dedicated to corona virus information under the Portuguese Health Ministerial [https://covid19.min-saude.pt/ covid19.min-saude.pt]. After sometime a new governmental site was created to deal with more generic information explaining the emergency status, public information and the exceptional measures in how to help business under [https://covid19estamoson.gov.pt/ Estamos On] (We are ON).\n\nThere are a lot of information available to the public about different areas under [https://covid19.min-saude.pt/materiais-de-divulgacao/ materiais-de-divulgacao/]. \n[[File:CARTAZES-COVID19-V25-02-2020 SINTOMAS.pdf|alt=Portuguese COVID-19 Symptoms|thumb|Portuguese COVID-19 Symptoms|392x392px]]\n\n== Hospitals for COVID-19 ==\nThe following is a list of the front line COVID-19 hospitals.<ref>{{cite web |title=Situa\u00e7\u00e3o em Portugal |url=https://www.dgs.pt/pagina-de-entrada3/corona-virus/situacao-em-portugal.aspx |website=www.dgs.pt |publisher=www.dgs.pt |accessdate=12 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable mw-collapsible\"\n|+\n!Region\n!Hospital\n!Adults\n!Pediatric\n|-\n| rowspan=\"4\" |ARS North\n|Braga\n|{{yes C|}}\n|\n|-\n|Santo Ant\u00f3nio\n|{{yes C|}}\n|\n|-\n|S\u00e3o Jo\u00e3o\n|{{yes C|}}\n|{{yes C|}}\n|-\n|Pedro Hispano\n|{{yes C|}}\n