ary 2020 events in Europe]]\n[[Category:2020 in Portugal]]\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in Europe|Portugal]]\n", "name_user": "Tiagomagalhaes", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eTimeline graphs:wrong recoveries number for 07/04", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_coronavirus_pandemic_in_Portugal"}
{"title_page": "Camillo Ruspoli, 4th Marquis of Boadilla del Monte", "text_new": "{{Infobox royalty\n| consort = yes\n| spouse = Countess Emilia Orlandini del Beccuto\n| title = [[:es:Marquesado de Boadilla del Monte|Marquis of Boadilla del Monte]]\n| name = Camillo Ruspoli Landi\n| full name = Camillo Carlo Luigi Ruspoli Landi\n| succession = \n4th [[:es:Marquesado de Boadilla del Monte|Marquis of Boadilla del Monte]]\n| predecessor = [[Luigi Ruspoli, 3rd Marquis of Boadilla del Monte|Prince Luigi Ruspoli y Godoy]] \n| successor = [[Paolo Ruspoli, 5th Marquis of Boadilla del Monte|Prince Paolo Ruspoli]]\n| image = \n| caption =\n| reign = 1893-1944\n| issue = * Prince Luigi Francesco Maria Ruspoli\n* [[Paolo Ruspoli, 5th Marquis of Boadilla del Monte|Prince Paolo Ruspoli]]\n|residence= Villa Ruspoli (Florence)\n| house = [[Ruspoli]]\n| father = [[Luigi Ruspoli, 3rd Marquis of Boadilla del Monte|Prince Luigi Ruspoli y Godoy]]\n| mother = Emilia Landi\n| birth_date  = {{Birth date|1865|1|16|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Florence]], [[Kingdom of Italy]]\n| death_date  = {{Death date|1944|11|7|df=y}}\n| death_place = [[Florence]], [[Kingdom of Italy]]\n| religion = [[Catholic Church|Roman Catholic Church]]\n| signature =\n}}\n\n'''[[Don (honorific)|Don]] Camillo Carlo Luigi dei Principi Ruspoli''' (16 January 1865 in [[Florence]] &ndash; 7 November 1944 in Florence) was an [[Italian people|Italian]] and [[Spanish people|Spanish]] aristocrat, son of [[Luigi Ruspoli, 3rd Marquis of Boadilla del Monte|Luigi Ruspoli y Godoy, 3rd Marquis of Boadilla del Monte]] and second wife ''[[Don (honorific)|Donna]]'' Emilia, Nobile Landi.\n\nHe was '''4th Marqu\u00e9s de [[Boadilla del Monte]]''' with a [[Coat of Arms]] of Ruspoli (Letter of 28 March 1894) and [[Princes of the Holy Roman Empire|Prince of the Holy Roman Empire]].\n\n== Marriage and children ==\nOn 7 October 1897, in Florence, he married Emilia dei Conti Orlandini del Beccuto (18 April 1873 in Florence \u2013 ?), by whom he had two sons: \n* Don Luigi Francesco Maria [[Ruspoli family|dei Principi Ruspoli]] (31 August 1898 in [[Montughi]], [[Florence]] &ndash; 6 November 1944 in Florence), unmarried and without issue\n* '''[[Paolo Ruspoli, 5th Marquis of Boadilla del Monte]]'''\n\n== Additional information ==\n=== See also ===\n* [[Ruspoli]]\n\n=== Sources ===\n{{refbegin}}\n* {{cite book |last= Affonso  |first= Domingos de Ara\u00fajo|author2=Valdez, Rui Dique Travassos  |title=Livro de Oiro da Nobreza |format=3 volumes |volume=II |year=1938 |location=Lisbon |language=Portuguese }}\n* {{Cite web |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120415141444/http://grandesp.org.uk/historia/titulos/titintro.htm |title=Grandes de Espa\u00f1a |last=Hobbs |first=Nicolas |authorlink= |year=2007 |publisher= |location= |pages= |language=Spanish |doi= |archivedate=2012-04-15 |quote= }}\n* {{cite book |last=Instituto de Salazar y Castro |others=periodic publication |title=Elenco de Grandezas y Titulos Nobiliarios Espa\u00f1oles |language=Spanish }}\n* {{Cite web |url=http://genealogy.euweb.cz/other/ruspoli.html |title=Ruspoli de Godoy Genealogy |accessdate=15 February 2009 |author= |last= |first= |authorlink= |year=2007 |publisher= |location= |pages= |language= |doi= |archiveurl= |archivedate= |quote= }}{{Self-published source|date=August 2012}}{{Better source|date=August 2012}}\n{{refend}}\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-reg|es}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Luigi Ruspoli, 3rd Marquis of Boadilla del Monte|Luigi Ruspoli]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title= [[Marquis|Marqu\u00e9s]] of [[Boadilla del Monte]] |years=1893-1944}}\n{{s-aft|after={{nowrap|[[Paolo Ruspoli, 5th Marquis of Boadilla del Monte|Paolo Ruspoli]]}}}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Ruspoli, Camillo 04}}\n[[Category:1865 births]]\n[[Category:1944 deaths]]\n[[Category:House of Ruspoli|Camillo]]\n[[Category:Marquesses of Boadilla del Monte]]\n\n\n\n{{Spain-noble-stub}}\n{{italy-noble-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox royalty\n| consort = yes\n| spouse = Countess Emilia Orlandini del Beccuto\n| title = [[:es:Marquesado de Boadilla del Monte|Marquis of Boadilla del Monte]]\n| name = Camillo Ruspoli Landi\n| full name = Camillo Carlo Luigi Ruspoli Landi\n| succession = \n4th [[:es:Marquesado de Boadilla del Monte|Marquis of Boadilla del Monte]]\n| predecessor = [[Luigi Ruspoli, 3rd Marquis of Boadilla del Monte|Prince Luigi Ruspoli y Godoy]] \n| successor = [[Paolo Ruspoli, 5th Marquis of Boadilla del Monte|Prince Paolo Ruspoli]]\n| image = Villa ruspoli da s.marta 04.JPG\n| caption = Villa Ruspoli of the Marquesses of Boadilla del Monte in Florence\n| reign = 1893-1944\n| issue = * Prince Luigi Francesco Maria Ruspoli\n* [[Paolo Ruspoli, 5th Marquis of Boadilla del Monte|Prince Paolo Ruspoli]]\n|residence= Villa Ruspoli (Florence)\n| house = [[Ruspoli]]\n| father = [[Luigi Ruspoli, 3rd Marquis of Boadilla del Monte|Prince Luigi Ruspoli y Godoy]]\n| mother = Emilia Landi\n| birth_date  = {{Birth date|1865|1|16|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Florence]], [[Kingdom of Italy]]\n| death_date  = {{Death date|1944|11|7|df=y}}\n| death_place = [[Florence]], [[Kingdom of Italy]]\n| religion = [[Catholic Church|Roman Catholic Church]]\n| signature =\n}}\n\n'''[[Don (honorific)|Don]] Camillo Carlo Luigi dei Principi Ruspoli''' (16 January 1865 in [[Florence]] &ndash; 7 November 1944 in Florence) was an [[Italian people|Italian]] and [[Spanish people|Spanish]] aristocrat, son of [[Luigi Ruspoli, 3rd Marquis of Boadilla del Monte|Luigi Ruspoli y Godoy, 3rd Marquis of Boadilla del Monte]] and second wife ''[[Don (honorific)|Donna]]'' Emilia, Nobile Landi.\n\nHe was '''4th Marqu\u00e9s de [[Boadilla del Monte]]''' with a [[Coat of Arms]] of Ruspoli (Letter of 28 March 1894) and [[Princes of the Holy Roman Empire|Prince of the Holy Roman Empire]].\n\n== Marriage and children ==\nOn 7 October 1897, in Florence, he married Emilia dei Conti Orlandini del Beccuto (18 April 1873 in Florence \u2013 ?), by whom he had two sons: \n* Don Luigi Francesco Maria [[Ruspoli family|dei Principi Ruspoli]] (31 August 1898 in [[Montughi]], [[Florence]] &ndash; 6 November 1944 in Florence), unmarried and without issue\n* '''[[Paolo Ruspoli, 5th Marquis of Boadilla del Monte]]'''\n\n== Additional information ==\n=== See also ===\n* [[Ruspoli]]\n\n=== Sources ===\n{{refbegin}}\n* {{cite book |last= Affonso  |first= Domingos de Ara\u00fajo|author2=Valdez, Rui Dique Travassos  |title=Livro de Oiro da Nobreza |format=3 volumes |volume=II |year=1938 |location=Lisbon |language=Portuguese }}\n* {{Cite web |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120415141444/http://grandesp.org.uk/historia/titulos/titintro.htm |title=Grandes de Espa\u00f1a |last=Hobbs |first=Nicolas |authorlink= |year=2007 |publisher= |location= |pages= |language=Spanish |doi= |archivedate=2012-04-15 |quote= }}\n* {{cite book |last=Instituto de Salazar y Castro |others=periodic publication |title=Elenco de Grandezas y Titulos Nobiliarios Espa\u00f1oles |language=Spanish }}\n* {{Cite web |url=http://genealogy.euweb.cz/other/ruspoli.html |title=Ruspoli de Godoy Genealogy |accessdate=15 February 2009 |author= |last= |first= |authorlink= |year=2007 |publisher= |location= |pages= |language= |doi= |archiveurl= |archivedate= |quote= }}{{Self-published source|date=August 2012}}{{Better source|date=August 2012}}\n{{refend}}\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-reg|es}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Luigi Ruspoli, 3rd Marquis of Boadilla del Monte|Luigi Ruspoli]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title= [[Marquis|Marqu\u00e9s]] of [[Boadilla del Monte]] |years=1893-1944}}\n{{s-aft|after={{nowrap|[[Paolo Ruspoli, 5th Marquis of Boadilla del Monte|Paolo Ruspoli]]}}}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Ruspoli, Camillo 04}}\n[[Category:1865 births]]\n[[Category:1944 deaths]]\n[[Category:House of Ruspoli|Camillo]]\n[[Category:Marquesses of Boadilla del Monte]]\n\n\n\n{{Spain-noble-stub}}\n{{italy-noble-stub}}\n", "name_user": "176.83.115.41", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Camillo_Ruspoli,_4th_Marquis_of_Boadilla_del_Monte"}
{"title_page": "Luigi Ruspoli, 3rd Marquis of Boadilla del Monte", "text_new": "{{Infobox royalty\n| consort = yes\n| spouse = 1st Matilde Martellini \n2nd Emilia Landi \n| title = [[:es:Marquesado de Boadilla del Monte|Marquis of Boadilla del Monte]]\n| name = Luigi Ruspoli y Godoy\n| full name = Luigi Ruspoli y Godoy\n| succession = \n3rd [[:es:Marquesado de Boadilla del Monte|Marquis of Boadilla del Monte]]\n| predecessor = [[Carlota de Godoy, 2nd Duchess of Sueca|Carlota Godoy and Bourbon]] \n| successor = [[Camillo Ruspoli, 4th Marquis of Boadilla del Monte|Prince Camillo Ruspoli]]\n| image = \n| caption =\n| reign = 1886-1893\n| issue = * Princess Carlota Camilla Luisa Ruspoli\n* [[Camillo Ruspoli, 4th Marquis of Boadilla del Monte|Prince Camillo Ruspoli]]\n|residence= Villa Ruspoli (Florence)\n| house = [[Ruspoli]]\n| father = [[Camillo Ruspoli, Duke of Sueca|Prince Camillo Ruspoli]]\n| mother = [[Carlota de Godoy, 2nd Duchess of Sueca|Carlota Godoy and Bourbon]]\n| birth_date  = {{Birth date|1828|8|22}}\n| birth_place = [[Florence]], [[Grand Duchy of Tuscany]]\n| death_date  = {{Death date|1893|12|21}}\n| death_place = [[Florence]], [[Kingdom of Italy]]\n| religion = [[Catholic Church|Roman Catholic Church]]\n| signature =\n}}\n\n'''Don Luigi Ruspoli y Godoy, de Khevenh\u00fcller-Metsch y Borb\u00f3n, dei Principi Ruspoli''' (August 22, 1828 in [[Florence]] &ndash; December 21, 1893 in Florence) was an [[Italian people|Italian]] and [[Spanish people|Spanish]] aristocrat, son of the [[Camillo Ruspoli, Duke of Sueca|Prince Camillo Ruspoli]] and wife [[Carlota de Godoy, 2nd Duchess of Sueca|Carlota de Godoy y Borb\u00f3n, 2nd Duchess of Sueca]].\n\nHe was 3rd Marqu\u00e9s de [[Boadilla del Monte]] with a [[Coat of Arms]] of Ruspoli (Letter of May 8, 1853) and [[Princes of the Holy Roman Empire|Prince of the Holy Roman Empire]], [[Knight]] of Honour of the [[Sovereign Military Order of Malta]], etc.\n\n== Marriages and children ==\n[[File:Carlota Godoy, por Luis de la Cruz.jpg|thumb|Carlota Godoy y Borb\u00f3n, II Duchess of Sueca, II Marchioness of Boadilla del Monte]]\nHe married firstly in [[Florence]], August 5, 1852 [[Don (honorific)|Donna]] Matilde Martellini (November 13, 1818/1819 in Florence, November 13 &ndash; September 8, 1855 in Florence), legitimate daughter of the Marchese Martellini, who was a Mayor (''Majordomo-Maggiore'') of the Palace of the Grand Duchess of [[Grand Duchy of Tuscany|Tuscany]], by whom he had a daughter: \n\n* [[Don (honorific)|Donna]] Carlota Camilla Luisa [[Ruspoli family|dei Principi Ruspoli]] (April 5, 1854 in Florence &ndash; September 1, 1930 in [[Nice]]) married in [[Florence]], September 4, 1872/1892 Enrico, Conte Casalini (1846\u20131907), by whom she had an only daughter:\n** ''[[Matilda, Contessa Casalini]] (1873 in Florence &ndash; 1941 in Nice), unmarried and without issue''\n\nHe married secondly in [[Florence]], February 7, 1863  [[Nobile (aristocracy)|Nobile]] Emilia Landi (June 25/26, 1824 in Florence &ndash; January 5, 1894 in Florence), by whom he had a son:  \n* '''[[Camillo Ruspoli, 4th Marquis of Boadilla del Monte]]'''\n\n== Additional information ==\n=== See also ===\n* [[Ruspoli]]\n\n=== Sources ===\n{{refbegin}}\n* {{cite book |last= Affonso |first= Domingos de Ara\u00fajo|author2=Valdez, Rui Dique Travassos  |title=Livro de Oiro da Nobreza |format=3 volumes |volume=II |year=1938 |location=Lisbon |language=Portuguese }}\n* {{Cite web |url=http://grandesp.org.uk/historia/titulos/titintro.htm |title=Grandes de Espa\u00f1a |accessdate=15 October 2008 |last=Hobbs |first=Nicolas |authorlink= |year=2007 |website= |location= |pages= |language=Spanish |doi= |archiveurl= |archivedate= |quote= }}\n* {{cite book |last=Instituto de Salazar y Castro |others=periodic publication |title=Elenco de Grandezas y Titulos Nobiliarios Espa\u00f1oles |language=Spanish }}\n* {{Cite web |url=http://genealogy.euweb.cz/other/ruspoli.html |title=Ruspoli de Godoy Genealogy |accessdate=15 Feb