{"title_page": "Marcantonio Mario Dimitri Ruspoli, 3rd Prince of Poggio Suasa", "text_new": "{{unreferenced|date=September 2018}}\n{{Infobox royalty\n| consort = yes\n| spouse = {{plain list|\n* L\u00facia Helena Pessoa de Mello\n* Gleide Chagas Portela\n}}\n| name = Marcantonio Mario Ruspoli\n| full name = Marcantonio Mario Dimitri dei Principi Ruspoli\n| succession = [[Castelleone di Suasa|Prince of Poggio Suasa]]\n| predecessor = [[Mario Ruspoli, 2nd Prince of Poggio Suasa|Prince Mario Ruspoli]] \n| successor = [[Costantino Mario Ruspoli, 4th Prince of Poggio Suasa|Prince Costantino Ruspoli]]\n| image =\n| caption =\n| reign = 1963\u20132003 \n| issue = {{plain list|\n*Princess Adriana Ruspoli\n*Princess Elisabeth Ruspoli\n*Princess Christiane Ruspoli\n*[[Costantino Mario Ruspoli, 4th Prince of Poggio Suasa|Prince Costantino Ruspoli]]\n*Princess Diana Ruspoli\n*Prince Pietro Ruspoli\n}}\n| house = [[Ruspoli]]\n| father = Prince Constantino Ruspoli\n| mother = Countess Elisabeth Catherine van der Noot d'Assche\n| birth_date  = {{Birth date|mf=yes|1926|11|28}} \n| birth_place = [[Etterbeek]], [[Brussels]], Belgium\n| death_date  = {{Death date and age|mf=yes|2003|8|1|1926|11|28}} \n| death_place = [[Recife]], [[Pernambuco]], Brazil\n| religion = [[Catholic Church|Roman Catholic Church]]\n| signature =\n}}\n\n'''Marcantonio Mario Dimitri dei Principi Ruspoli''' (November 28, 1926 &ndash; August 1, 2003) was the 3rd Principe di [[Castelleone di Suasa|Poggio Suasa]] and [[Princes of the Holy Roman Empire|Prince of the Holy Roman Empire]], son of Costantino Ruspoli (Costantino is an eldest son of [[Mario Ruspoli, 2nd Prince of Poggio Suasa]]), and wife Elisabeth Catherine Adrienne Marie Anne Comtesse van der Noot d'Assche.\n\n== Marriages and children ==\nHe married firstly at [[Recife]], [[Pernambuco]], November 17, 1951 and divorced in 1958 L\u00facia Helena Pessoa de Mello (April 22, 1922 &ndash;), a [[Portuguese Brazilian]], without issue.\n\nHe married secondly at [[Macei\u00f3]], [[Alagoas]], September 8, 1981 Gleide Chagas Portela ([[Catende]], [[Pernambuco]], November 18, 1935 &ndash; [[Recife]], [[Pernambuco]], July 3, 1992), a [[Portuguese Brazilian]], daughter of Pedro Chagas and wife Nat\u00e1lia Portela, by whom he had six children:\n\n* Donna Adriana dei Principi Ruspoli-Poggio Suasa ([[Recife]], [[Pernambuco]], February 27, 1963 &ndash;), unmarried and without issue.\n* Donna Elizabeth dei Principi Ruspoli-Poggio Suasa ([[Recife]], [[Pernambuco]], January 17, 1965 &ndash;), married at [[Recife]], [[Pernambuco]], December 2, 1990 Natanael Gon\u00e7alves, by whom she had an only daughter:\n** ''Nataly  Gon\u00e7alves ([[S\u00e3o Paulo]], [[S\u00e3o Paulo (state)|S\u00e3o Paulo]], September 2, 1994 &ndash;)''.\n* Donna Christiane dei Principi Ruspoli-Poggio Suasa ([[Recife]], [[Pernambuco]], January 25, 1968 &ndash;), married on March 31, 1990 Jos\u00e9 Portella de Macedo, Jr., by whom she had an only son:\n** ''Jos\u00e9 Eduardo  Portella de Macedo ([[Manaus]], [[Amazonas (Brazilian state)|Amazonas]], March 17, 1991 &ndash;) married on April 26, 2014 Thamires Gomes Lima.''\n* '''[[Costantino Mario Ruspoli, 4th Prince of Poggio Suasa]].'''\n*Donna Diana dei Principi Ruspoli-Poggio Suasa ([[Recife]], [[Pernambuco]], March 5, 1973 &ndash;), married in [[Recife]], [[Pernambuco]], June 2, 2002 F\u00e1bio Miguel Santos, by whom she had an only son:\n** ''F\u00e1bio Henrique Miguel Santos ([[Recife]], [[Pernambuco]], 2005 &ndash;)''.\n* Don Pietro Marco dei Principi Ruspoli-Poggio Suasa ([[Macei\u00f3]], [[Alagoas]], March 25, 1981 &ndash; [[Macei\u00f3]], [[Alagoas]], March 28, 1981).\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Ruspoli]]\n\n== External links ==\n* [http://www.geneall.net/I/per_page.php?id=598255 Marcantonio Mario Dimitri Ruspoli on a genealogical site]\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-reg|it}}\n{{succession box|before= [[Mario Ruspoli, 2nd Prince of Poggio Suasa]] | title= [[Castelleone di Suasa|3rd Prince of Poggio Suasa]] | after=[[Costantino Mario Ruspoli, 4th Prince of Poggio Suasa]]| years=1963\u20132003}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Ruspoli, Marcantonio Mario Dimitri, 3rd Prince Of Poggio Suasa}}\n[[Category:1926 births]]\n[[Category:2003 deaths]]\n[[Category:House of Ruspoli|Mercantonio]]\n[[Category:Italian nobility]]\n", "text_old": "{{unreferenced|date=September 2018}}\n{{Infobox royalty\n| consort = yes\n| spouse = {{plain list|\n* L\u00facia Helena Pessoa de Mello\n* Gleide Chagas Portela\n}}\n| name = Marcantonio Mario Ruspoli\n| full name = Marcantonio Mario Dimitri dei Principi Ruspoli\n| succession = [[Castelleone di Suasa|Prince of Poggio Suasa]]\n| predecessor = [[Mario Ruspoli, 2nd Prince of Poggio Suasa|Prince Mario Ruspoli]] \n| successor = [[Costantino Mario Ruspoli, 4th Prince of Poggio Suasa|Prince Costantino Ruspoli]]\n| image = Arme famiglia Ruspoli di Roma.jpg\n| caption =\n| reign = 1963\u20132003 \n| issue = {{plain list|\n*Princess Adriana Ruspoli\n*Princess Elisabeth Ruspoli\n*Princess Christiane Ruspoli\n*[[Costantino Mario Ruspoli, 4th Prince of Poggio Suasa|Prince Costantino Ruspoli]]\n*Princess Diana Ruspoli\n*Prince Pietro Ruspoli\n}}\n| house = [[Ruspoli]]\n| father = Prince Constantino Ruspoli\n| mother = Countess Elisabeth Catherine van der Noot d'Assche\n| birth_date  = {{Birth date|mf=yes|1926|11|28}} \n| birth_place = [[Etterbeek]], [[Brussels]], Belgium\n| death_date  = {{Death date and age|mf=yes|2003|8|1|1926|11|28}} \n| death_place = [[Recife]], [[Pernambuco]], Brazil\n| religion = [[Catholic Church|Roman Catholic Church]]\n| signature =\n}}\n\n'''Marcantonio Mario Dimitri dei Principi Ruspoli''' (November 28, 1926 &ndash; August 1, 2003) was the 3rd Principe di [[Castelleone di Suasa|Poggio Suasa]] and [[Princes of the Holy Roman Empire|Prince of the Holy Roman Empire]], son of Costantino Ruspoli (Costantino is an eldest son of [[Mario Ruspoli, 2nd Prince of Poggio Suasa]]), and wife Elisabeth Catherine Adrienne Marie Anne Comtesse van der Noot d'Assche.\n\n== Marriages and children ==\nHe married firstly at [[Recife]], [[Pernambuco]], November 17, 1951 and divorced in 1958 L\u00facia Helena Pessoa de Mello (April 22, 1922 &ndash;), a [[Portuguese Brazilian]], without issue.\n\nHe married secondly at [[Macei\u00f3]], [[Alagoas]], September 8, 1981 Gleide Chagas Portela ([[Catende]], [[Pernambuco]], November 18, 1935 &ndash; [[Recife]], [[Pernambuco]], July 3, 1992), a [[Portuguese Brazilian]], daughter of Pedro Chagas and wife Nat\u00e1lia Portela, by whom he had six children:\n\n* Donna Adriana dei Principi Ruspoli-Poggio Suasa ([[Recife]], [[Pernambuco]], February 27, 1963 &ndash;), unmarried and without issue.\n* Donna Elizabeth dei Principi Ruspoli-Poggio Suasa ([[Recife]], [[Pernambuco]], January 17, 1965 &ndash;), married at [[Recife]], [[Pernambuco]], December 2, 1990 Natanael Gon\u00e7alves, by whom she had an only daughter:\n** ''Nataly  Gon\u00e7alves ([[S\u00e3o Paulo]], [[S\u00e3o Paulo (state)|S\u00e3o Paulo]], September 2, 1994 &ndash;)''.\n* Donna Christiane dei Principi Ruspoli-Poggio Suasa ([[Recife]], [[Pernambuco]], January 25, 1968 &ndash;), married on March 31, 1990 Jos\u00e9 Portella de Macedo, Jr., by whom she had an only son:\n** ''Jos\u00e9 Eduardo  Portella de Macedo ([[Manaus]], [[Amazonas (Brazilian state)|Amazonas]], March 17, 1991 &ndash;) married on April 26, 2014 Thamires Gomes Lima.''\n* '''[[Costantino Mario Ruspoli, 4th Prince of Poggio Suasa]].'''\n*Donna Diana dei Principi Ruspoli-Poggio Suasa ([[Recife]], [[Pernambuco]], March 5, 1973 &ndash;), married in [[Recife]], [[Pernambuco]], June 2, 2002 F\u00e1bio Miguel Santos, by whom she had an only son:\n** ''F\u00e1bio Henrique Miguel Santos ([[Recife]], [[Pernambuco]], 2005 &ndash;)''.\n* Don Pietro Marco dei Principi Ruspoli-Poggio Suasa ([[Macei\u00f3]], [[Alagoas]], March 25, 1981 &ndash; [[Macei\u00f3]], [[Alagoas]], March 28, 1981).\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Ruspoli]]\n\n== External links ==\n* [http://www.geneall.net/I/per_page.php?id=598255 Marcantonio Mario Dimitri Ruspoli on a genealogical site]\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-reg|it}}\n{{succession box|before= [[Mario Ruspoli, 2nd Prince of Poggio Suasa]] | title= [[Castelleone di Suasa|3rd Prince of Poggio Suasa]] | after=[[Costantino Mario Ruspoli, 4th Prince of Poggio Suasa]]| years=1963\u20132003}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Ruspoli, Marcantonio Mario Dimitri, 3rd Prince Of Poggio Suasa}}\n[[Category:1926 births]]\n[[Category:2003 deaths]]\n[[Category:House of Ruspoli|Mercantonio]]\n[[Category:Italian nobility]]\n", "name_user": "176.83.115.41", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Marcantonio_Mario_Dimitri_Ruspoli,_3rd_Prince_of_Poggio_Suasa"}
