and without issue, was the 1st Prince of Candriano (formerly Marquis of Candriano) (12 May 1893 \u2013 1 October 1920).<ref>[http://www.prolococastelbaronia.it/documenti%20sc/IRPINIA%20TERRA%20DA%20RISCOPRIRE%20SECONDA%20ANNUALITA.pdf The granting of prince of (I) Candriano title by the king Umberto I of Italy (1893) ] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111004120121/http://www.prolococastelbaronia.it/documenti%20sc/IRPINIA%20TERRA%20DA%20RISCOPRIRE%20SECONDA%20ANNUALITA.pdf |date=2011-10-04 }}</ref><ref>[http://www.genmarenostrum.com/pagine-lettere/letterac/Caracciolo/caracciolo-torella.htm I Caracciolo di Torella]</ref>\n\n== Marriage and child ==\nHe married in Rome, April 29, 1905 Baronne Marie Marguerite Blanc (daughter of [[French nobility|French]] Baron Albert Blanc and wife Natalia [[Terry]] y Dortic\u00f3s) ([[Madrid]], May 7, 1884 &ndash; November 22, 1961), by whom he had an only son:\n\n* Don Emanuele Alberto dei Principi Ruspoli ([[Rome]], February 24, 1906 &ndash; [[Paris]], August 31, 1929), unmarried and without issue.\n\n== Notable published works ==\nHe composed the ballet fantasy ''Festival of the Gnomes'' (which was orchestrated, conducted and recorded by [[Les Baxter]] in 1951).<ref>[http://aura-archangemaudit.blogspot.com/2008/09/festival-of-gnomes-prince-di-candriano.html Festival Of The Gnomes] ([[Spanish language|in Spanish]])</ref><ref>[http://www.worldcat.org/title/festival-of-the-gnomes-the-music-of-prince-di-candriano/oclc/013640115 Festival of the gnomes : the music of Prince Di Candriano.]</ref>\n\n== Ancestry ==\n{{ahnentafel\n|collapsed=yes |align=center\n|boxstyle_1=background-color: #fcc;\n|boxstyle_2=background-color: #fb9;\n|boxstyle_3=background-color: #ffc;\n|boxstyle_4=background-color: #bfc;\n|boxstyle_5=background-color: #9fe;\n|1= 1. '''Prince Camillo Ruspoli, 2nd Prince of Candriano'''\n|2= 2. [[Emanuele Ruspoli, 1st Prince of Poggio Suasa|Emanuele Francesco Ruspoli, 1st Prince of Poggio Suasa]]\n|3= 3. Laura [[